# NPTEL Hub Backend

## Environment Setup

Create a `.env` file in the server directory:

```env
# Server Configuration
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development

# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/nptel-hub

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_change_in_production

# Frontend
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Email Configuration
EMAIL_USER=your_email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your_gmail_app_password

# AWS S3 (Optional)
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_aws_key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_aws_secret
AWS_S3_BUCKET_NAME=your_bucket_name

# Firebase (Optional Alternative)
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_firebase_project
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=your_firebase_key
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=your_firebase_email
```

## Installation

```bash
npm install
```

## Running Locally

Development mode with auto-reload:
```bash
npm run dev
```

Production mode:
```bash
npm start
```

## API Documentation

### Authentication Endpoints
- `POST /api/auth/register` - Register new user
- `POST /api/auth/login` - Login user
- `POST /api/auth/verify-email` - Verify email
- `POST /api/auth/forgot-password` - Request password reset
- `POST /api/auth/reset-password` - Reset password
- `GET /api/auth/me` - Get current user
- `PUT /api/auth/profile` - Update profile
- `POST /api/auth/change-password` - Change password
- `POST /api/auth/logout` - Logout

### Course Endpoints
- `GET /api/courses/subjects` - Get all subjects
- `GET /api/courses/subjects/:slug` - Get subject by slug
- `GET /api/courses/courses/subject/:subjectId` - Get courses by subject
- `GET /api/courses/courses/code/:code` - Get course by code

### Week & Year Instance Endpoints
- `GET /api/weeks/year-instances/:courseId` - Get all year instances
- `GET /api/weeks/year-instances/:id` - Get specific year instance
- `GET /api/weeks/weeks/:yearInstanceId` - Get weeks
- `GET /api/weeks/week/:id` - Get specific week
- `GET /api/weeks/week/:weekId/stats` - Get week statistics

### Resource Endpoints
- `GET /api/resources/resources/:weekId` - Get resources for week
- `GET /api/resources/resource/:id` - Get specific resource
- `POST /api/resources/resources` - Create resource (protected)
- `PUT /api/resources/resources/:id` - Update resource (protected)
- `DELETE /api/resources/resources/:id` - Delete resource (protected)
- `POST /api/resources/resources/:id/upvote` - Upvote resource (protected)
- `POST /api/resources/resources/:id/downvote` - Downvote resource (protected)
- `POST /api/resources/resources/:id/comments` - Add comment (protected)
- `POST /api/resources/resources/:id/report` - Report resource (protected)

## Socket.io Events (Real-time Chat)

### Client to Server
- `join-room` - Join a week's chat room
- `send-message` - Send message
- `edit-message` - Edit sent message
- `delete-message` - Delete message
- `add-reaction` - Add emoji reaction
- `report-message` - Report message
- `typing` - Notify typing
- `stop-typing` - Stop typing notification
- `leave-room` - Leave room

### Server to Client
- `message-history` - Initial message history
- `new-message` - New message broadcast
- `message-edited` - Message edits
- `message-deleted` - Message deletion
- `reaction-added` - Reaction updates
- `user-joined` - User join notification
- `user-left` - User leave notification
- `user-typing` - User typing indicator
- `error` - Error messages

## Database Schema

MongoDB collections with strict validation:
- **Users** - User accounts and profiles
- **Subjects** - Course subjects
- **Courses** - Individual courses
- **YearInstances** - Course instances by year/semester
- **Weeks** - Weekly content
- **Messages** - Real-time chat messages
- **Resources** - User-uploaded notes and links

